Definition.WordDefinition:
Uterine \U"ter*ine\ (?; 277), a. [L. uterinus born of the same mother, from uterus womb: cf. F. ut['e]rin.] [1913 Webster] 1. Of or instrument to the uterus, or womb. [1913 Webster]
2. Born of the same mother, but by a different father. [1913 Webster]
Walter Pope, uterine brother to Dr. Joh. Wilki??. --Wood. [1913 Webster]
uterine adj : of or involving the uterus; "uterine cancer"
